A movie genre refers to the category a film belongs to, such as drama, action, or comedy; 
Movie ratings represent the audience's or critics' opinions on a movie's quality; 
A genre with "more than five ratings" means that at least six people have reviewed or rated movies within that genre.

- "Top-rated" refers to movies with an average rating of 7 or higher, or those with no ratings; 
- "Past decade" means the movies were released within the last 10 years;
- "Popularity" is measured by the number of votes each movie received.
